    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (78.13) and **James Wood** (75.23) headline our offensive assault. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** benefits immensely from a favorable matchup against Spencer Arrighetti, with a combination of elite park factors and a generous 19% SP skill boost pushing his ceiling. His matchup against a pitcher with a slow delivery provides an immediate boost to our pursuit of stolen bases. Similarly, **James Wood** leverages a leadoff slot and a neutral platoon advantage to maximize his plate appearances, positioning him as a high-floor, high-upside play. **Corbin Carroll** (72.54) and **Mickey Moniak** (71.66) round out our top-tier tier, with **Mickey Moniak** specifically thriving on a massive 14% platoon boost despite the cautionary wind-in warning at the stadium.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was excluding **Jose Caballero**, whose score of 53.20 kept him in the conversation until the final iteration. While the matchup against Arrighetti is soft, his projected #9 slot and poor platoon splits relative to our other middle infield options ultimately capped his utility. **Austin Riley** (56.86) remains a volatile but necessary inclusion; despite a difficult matchup against Aaron Nola, his elite BvP history (60 PA) offers a distinct tactical edge that offsets his slightly lower base projection. We are closely monitoring the status of **Luis Campusano** and **Dalton Rushing**; as both are still currently listed as \"Lineup Pending,\" their efficiency scores remain tethered to historical lineup assumptions. Should either be dropped in their respective orders, we may see a significant re-evaluation of our efficiency floor, particularly for **Dalton Rushing**, whose score is already being held back by a negative platoon split against Shota Imanaga.",
